</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1350,1516]" pageId="2" pageNumber="62">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="62">
- Leaves typically green or yellow-green, leaf base typically reddish, contrasting from upper leaf; limbidium unistratose, strong or sometimes weak or rarely absent; pinkish to reddish subalar inflated auriculate group of cells present, at least on leaves of fertile shoots; costa percurrent to long-excurrent in distinct awn................................................................................ Subgenus 
