<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="62" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1562,1697]" pageId="2" pageNumber="62">Note that for many species sexuality is critical and mature capsules are needed as spore size and peristome development are also critical characters. Sterile material of many species cannot be unequivocally identified. Peristome reduction includes cilia shortened or typically absent, reduced endostome processes, and a low basal membrane (&lt;1/2 height of exostome) which is sometimes fused with the exostome.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
